The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                                   Business Briefs
                              
	 Mumbai, April 19: The countrys foreign exchange reserves rose $482 million to $312.36 billion for the week ended april 11 from $311.88 billion in the previous week. Foreign currency assets shot up to $301.82 billion during the period, up $426 million from $301.39 billion, the rbi said in its report. The FCAs expressed in us dollar include the effect of appreciation or depreciation of non-us currencies held in reserve. The reserve position in the international monetary fund rose $56 million to $490 million from $434 million. During the period, gold reserves and special drawing rights remained static at $10.03 billion and $18 million respectively, it added.                             
	 Toronto, April 19: Canada will open trade offices in Hyderabad and Calcutta. Canada is committed to strengthening ties with New Delhi, Prime Minister Stephen Harper said yesterday, adding his government had taken a number of steps to improve trade relations with India. Harper said this while presenting the Global Indian award to Sam Pitroda for his contributions to improving telecommunication services in India.
                                                                                                                               
